article.description: Ta'Shia Phillips had 22 points and 18 rebounds Saturday, leading No. 13 Xavier to a 75-47 victory over Fordham that clinched the Musketeers' second Atlantic 10 regular-season championship.
article.headline: No. 13 Xavier breezes past Fordham behind Phillips' double-double
article.linkText: Xavier tops Fordham, clinches Atlantic 10 title
article.story:
CINCINNATI -- Ta'Shia Phillips had 22 points and 18 rebounds Saturday, leading No. 13 Xavier to a 75-47 victory over Fordham that clinched the Musketeers' second Atlantic 10 regular-season championship.

Xavier (25-5, 13-1) cut down the nets after winning its first such title in eight years. The Musketeers finished third in the conference each of the last two seasons, but won its tournament.

Phillips' 14th double-double of the season set the tone against Fordham (8-21, 1-13), which didn't win a game last season. Randall Hurst led the Rams with 16 points.

The Musketeers won the title despite missing junior forward Amber Harris for the entire season following knee surgery. Harris, their top returning scorer and shot blocker from last season, returned to practice this week.
